 Unfortunately for our universities, Performance Contracting  has not only shifted from their main mandates, but also turned into a mere routine check.Teachers collaborate to score themselves highly, and placate their employer’s ego through timely online submission of reports.   It is not in doubt that any organisation worth its salt must subject itself to Quality Management System (QMS). This facilitates certification, whereupon the concerned parties seek feedback through relevant audits, paving way for improvement.
There are many avenues of QMS, most based on International Organization for Standardisation (ISO) 9001. Here, organisations commit themselves to particular world class specifications for products, services and systems, often expressed in terms of performance indicators.



